1
00:00:11,041 --> 00:00:18,291
[CORDELIA screaming]

2
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:32,291
[CORDELIA gasping, screaming]

3
00:00:33,583 --> 00:00:36,333
[MARQUIS] The gray Wolf pup
will be born on the same night

4
00:00:36,416 --> 00:00:39,500
that the savior
Jesus Christ was born.

5
00:00:39,583 --> 00:00:41,666
How very ironic indeed.

6
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:44,458
[CORDELIA gasping]

7
00:00:44,541 --> 00:00:47,291
[MARQUIS]
Such an unfortunate child...

8
00:00:47,375 --> 00:00:49,250
To be brought forth
from a wellspring

9
00:00:49,333 --> 00:00:52,125
of tainted blood and sin.

10
00:00:52,208 --> 00:00:53,916
I offer a grievous blessing.

11
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,000
[CORDELIA gasps]

12
00:02:29,416 --> 00:02:33,458
[KAZUYA panting]

13
00:02:40,625 --> 00:02:43,791
This is the first snow
I've seen in Saubure.

14
00:02:43,875 --> 00:02:45,208
And in a few weeks...

15
00:02:45,291 --> 00:02:47,583
...I'll have my first
Christmas here.

16
00:02:49,208 --> 00:02:50,458
[KAZUYA] Victorique,
you have to come with me

17
00:02:50,541 --> 00:02:51,500
to the Christmas party.

18
00:02:51,583 --> 00:02:53,166
It's supposed to be lots of fun.

19
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:56,291
And there's also a gift
exchange we can take part in.

20
00:02:56,375 --> 00:02:58,625
It doesn't make any sense
for a person to celebrate

21
00:02:58,708 --> 00:03:01,458
their own birthday by giving
someone else a present.

22
00:03:01,541 --> 00:03:04,125
Well, I do have to
agree with you on that.

23
00:03:04,208 --> 00:03:06,708
But giving out gifts is a
really fun holiday tradition

24
00:03:06,791 --> 00:03:09,416
that I happen to like a lot--

25
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:11,875
Did you mean because it's
Jesus Christ's birthday?

26
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:13,541
[VICTORIQUE]
It's not only his.

27
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:16,416
[KAZUYA]
Huh?!

28
00:03:17,708 --> 00:03:20,083
Since I'm shopping for a
birthday and Christmas present,

29
00:03:20,166 --> 00:03:21,708
it needs to be special!

30
00:03:21,791 --> 00:03:24,208
[enging revving]

31
00:03:24,291 --> 00:03:24,833
[KAZUYA gasps]

32
00:03:24,916 --> 00:03:27,041
[tires screeching]

33
00:03:31,458 --> 00:03:33,083
How's it going, Kujo?

34
00:03:33,166 --> 00:03:35,333
Uh-- Hey Miss Sophie!

35
00:03:35,416 --> 00:03:36,875
[SOPHIE]
Where are you headed?

36
00:03:36,958 --> 00:03:39,333
[KAZUYA] Oh. I'm just going
Christmas shopping in Saubreme.

37
00:03:39,416 --> 00:03:40,833
[SOPHIE]
What a coincidence!

38
00:03:40,916 --> 00:03:42,666
Hop on! I'll give you a lift.

39
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:43,500
[KAZUYA]
Thanks!

40
00:03:43,583 --> 00:03:44,958
Are you shopping, too?

41
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:47,083
No, the Phantom Theater is
putting on a Christmas play

42
00:03:47,166 --> 00:03:49,083
called "The Blue
Rose of Saubreme."

43
00:03:49,166 --> 00:03:50,875
That rings a bell.

44
00:03:50,958 --> 00:03:52,083
It must be about--

45
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:53,291
--[gasps]
--Here!

46
00:03:53,375 --> 00:03:55,375
You see? It's based
on the real life story

47
00:03:55,458 --> 00:03:57,750
of our most tragic
queen, Coco Rose!

48
00:03:57,833 --> 00:03:59,791
I've been a fan of hers
since I was a little girl.

49
00:03:59,875 --> 00:04:02,416
I wouldn't miss this
play for the world.

50
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:06,041
Hurry up and get on,
we can talk more later.

51
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:07,958
I appreciate the ride.

52
00:04:08,041 --> 00:04:09,625
I had no idea you
even knew how to

53
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:10,708
--drive a motorcycle.
--[engine revs]

54
00:04:10,791 --> 00:04:11,666
--I'm very impressed.
--[engine revs]

55
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:12,791
[SOPHIE]
Hm?

56
00:04:12,875 --> 00:04:14,791
This is my first time on one.

57
00:04:14,875 --> 00:04:16,500
[KAZUYA]
Huh?

58
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:20,708
[screaming]

59
00:04:34,041 --> 00:04:35,250
[VICTORIQUE]
Where is he?

60
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:38,416
[AVRIL panting]

61
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:39,583
Hey, Victorique!

62
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:41,541
[VICTORIQUE]
It's the farting newt.

63
00:04:41,625 --> 00:04:43,625
[AVRIL]
Do you know where Kujo's at?

64
00:04:43,708 --> 00:04:45,541
I was hoping he'd help me
get some stuff ready

65
00:04:45,625 --> 00:04:47,250
for the school's
Christmas party.

66
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:47,916
I know!

67
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,583
[screams]

68
00:04:49,666 --> 00:04:51,875
How about I tell you a
really spooky ghost story

69
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:53,250
while we wait for him?

70
00:04:53,333 --> 00:04:55,750
It'll be more fun
than a dumb book.

71
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:57,500
[VICTORIQUE growls]

72
00:05:00,625 --> 00:05:04,875
[VICTORIQUE panting]

73
00:05:04,958 --> 00:05:07,208
[AVRIL]
Um... Are you okay?

74
00:05:07,291 --> 00:05:08,291
Here's the deal.

75
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:10,291
You are not allowed
to take one step

76
00:05:10,375 --> 00:05:11,833
over this wall of knowledge.

77
00:05:11,916 --> 00:05:13,166
Do you understand me?

78
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:14,041
[AVRIL]
Huh?

79
00:05:14,125 --> 00:05:14,916
All right.

80
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:17,041
Now tell me this story of yours.

81
00:05:18,791 --> 00:05:20,583
It's about Coco Rose!

82
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:22,916
I'm sure you remember that
she's the beloved queen

83
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,833
Leviathan made
the blue rose for.

84
00:05:24,916 --> 00:05:26,208
[VICTORIQUE]
Of course.

85
00:05:26,291 --> 00:05:29,000
[AVRIL] Well, Queen Coco was
not able to have a baby.

86
00:05:29,083 --> 00:05:32,000
And King Rupert de Giret
reproached her for that.

87
00:05:32,083 --> 00:05:35,375
So he sent her away to live in
a country house with a maid.

88
00:05:35,458 --> 00:05:37,666
[VICTORIQUE] When is this
going to get interesting?

89
00:05:37,750 --> 00:05:40,250
[AVRIL] Be patient!
I'm setting up the story!

90
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:43,708
Anyway, Leviathan had
given her a magical rock.

91
00:05:43,791 --> 00:05:45,458
And whenever she
held that stone,

92
00:05:45,541 --> 00:05:48,000
it gave her the ability
to turn invisible.

93
00:05:48,083 --> 00:05:49,833
Thanks to that powerful gift,

94
00:05:49,916 --> 00:05:52,375
Queen Coco was able to
slip past the guards

95
00:05:52,458 --> 00:05:54,916
and sneak out of her prison
to actually have some fun.

96
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,958
[VICTORIQUE]
Hm...

97
00:05:57,041 --> 00:06:01,000
A young queen locked
away in a country house.

98
00:06:01,083 --> 00:06:04,583
And a magical rock that
helped her escape captivity.

99
00:06:16,583 --> 00:06:18,375
[VICTORIQUE]
Well, I guess his head is

100
00:06:18,458 --> 00:06:20,041
as dense as a rock, at least.

101
00:06:20,125 --> 00:06:21,208
[AVRIL]
Huh?

102
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:25,750
[ROSCOE]
"The Blue Rose of Saubreme."

103
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:27,958
I shouldn't be surprised
that Marquis de Blois

104
00:06:28,041 --> 00:06:30,333
is the one putting
on this damn play.

105
00:06:30,416 --> 00:06:33,333
And, of course,
it's on Christmas.

106
00:06:33,416 --> 00:06:37,041
The sacred night he tainted
with your humiliation.

107
00:06:37,125 --> 00:06:40,666
But I doubt he did all this
simply as some twisted joke.

108
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:43,416
There has to be a reason
he picked this specific play

109
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:46,375
to be performed on
this specific night.

110
00:06:46,458 --> 00:06:49,750
Ugh! That man is such a coward.

111
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:52,750
Doesn't he have better things
to do than try to hurt you?

112
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:57,000
[CORDELIA humming]

113
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:59,041
[ROSCOE]
Such a rosy life.

114
00:06:59,125 --> 00:07:01,250
But if the rose is blue...

115
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:03,083
...that changes everything.

116
00:07:09,541 --> 00:07:11,583
[DANCER A] Oh, just hurry
up and pack it in there.

117
00:07:11,666 --> 00:07:14,166
[DANCER B] Hey! Has
anyone seen my eyelashes?

118
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:15,541
[GINGER]
Cordelia.

119
00:07:15,625 --> 00:07:17,833
The red-haired boy is
in the audience again.

120
00:07:17,916 --> 00:07:19,208
[CORDELIA]
Yeah.

121
00:07:19,291 --> 00:07:21,625
I promised to meet him
after tonight's performance.

122
00:07:21,708 --> 00:07:23,833
[GINGER laughs]
Well, look at you!

123
00:07:23,916 --> 00:07:25,166
Be careful though.

124
00:07:25,250 --> 00:07:27,375
The quiet types are known
to have wandering hands!

125
00:07:27,458 --> 00:07:29,500
Oh, he would never try
something like that,

126
00:07:29,583 --> 00:07:31,458
and besides he's just a child.

127
00:07:31,541 --> 00:07:32,750
[GINGER]
Hm...

128
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:35,916
How old is that
necklace of yours?

129
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,375
You should get the redhead
to buy you a new one.

130
00:07:42,791 --> 00:07:44,083
No way.

131
00:07:44,166 --> 00:07:47,166
This is proof that I've
taken ownership of my past.

132
00:07:48,666 --> 00:07:49,500
[whistling]

133
00:07:49,583 --> 00:07:50,500
--[CORDELIA gasps]
--Our cue!

134
00:07:50,583 --> 00:07:52,041
Better hurry!

135
00:07:52,125 --> 00:07:53,666
La vie en rose!

136
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:55,416
[GINGER]
La vie en rose!

137
00:07:57,666 --> 00:08:00,583
[applause]

138
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:02,041
Cordelia!

139
00:08:02,125 --> 00:08:03,958
[whistles]

140
00:08:04,041 --> 00:08:09,791
[PERFORMERS] ♪ I have no tarts
or macarons I can spare ♪

141
00:08:09,875 --> 00:08:13,416
♪ There's just crunchy,
crusty bread to go around ♪

142
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:15,041
♪ No fair ♪

143
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:18,916
[PERFORMERS] ♪ There isn't
a Prince Charming ♪

144
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:21,916
♪ No brave knight
to come save me ♪

145
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,833
♪ But I honestly don't care ♪

146
00:08:23,916 --> 00:08:25,166
♪ No, no ♪

147
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:26,458
♪ I'm free ♪

148
00:08:26,541 --> 00:08:29,458
♪ 'Cause I do ♪

149
00:08:29,541 --> 00:08:32,708
♪ Have my love from you ♪

150
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:36,208
[PERFORMERS]
♪ Don't worry ♪

151
00:08:36,291 --> 00:08:37,333
♪ You've got me ♪

152
00:08:37,416 --> 00:08:40,583
♪ I know it sounds naïve ♪

153
00:08:40,666 --> 00:08:42,000
♪ We'll be okay ♪

154
00:08:42,083 --> 00:08:43,500
♪ Don't you cry ♪

155
00:08:43,583 --> 00:08:44,958
♪ We'll give 'em a show ♪

156
00:08:45,041 --> 00:08:49,625
♪ Grab my hand and away we go! ♪

157
00:08:52,541 --> 00:08:54,458
♪ It's a rosy life ♪

158
00:08:54,541 --> 00:08:55,916
♪ Rosy life ♪

159
00:08:56,000 --> 00:09:02,416
♪ La vie en rose!
La vie en rose! ♪

160
00:09:03,875 --> 00:09:05,791
[CORDELIA gasps]

161
00:09:13,666 --> 00:09:15,791
[MARQUIS] Looks like I've
caught myself a Gray Wolf.

162
00:09:15,875 --> 00:09:16,958
[CORDELIA gasps]

163
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,875
Hey, Cordelia!

164
00:09:19,958 --> 00:09:20,916
[gasps]

165
00:09:39,875 --> 00:09:41,708
[chuckles]

166
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:44,958
[ROSCOE gasps]

167
00:09:45,041 --> 00:09:45,958
--[clap]
--[CORDELIA gasps]

168
00:09:49,291 --> 00:09:52,000
[ROSCOE groans]

169
00:09:54,166 --> 00:09:59,291
[CORDELIA gasps, screams]

170
00:10:02,291 --> 00:10:03,333
[DOCTOR]
Marquis de Blois,

171
00:10:03,416 --> 00:10:05,375
the baby's crowning.

172
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:08,833
[MARQUIS]
My little Gray Wolf.

173
00:10:08,916 --> 00:10:12,166
You've been a guest of
mine for a year now.

174
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:15,750
The time has come for you to
actually be of some use to me.

175
00:10:16,791 --> 00:10:18,791
Our blood is mixed together.

176
00:10:18,875 --> 00:10:21,333
Wolf and human are now one.

177
00:10:21,416 --> 00:10:23,250
A child of destiny...

178
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:25,208
...will finally be born.

179
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:27,125
Arriving to purify
the corruption

180
00:10:27,208 --> 00:10:29,291
and cut through the storm.

181
00:10:29,375 --> 00:10:32,750
Now do your part
and give me power.

182
00:10:35,791 --> 00:10:40,583
[gasping

183
00:10:40,666 --> 00:10:43,916
[screams]

184
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:49,666
[ROSCOE]
Cordelia...

185
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:50,666
Cordelia!

186
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:51,916
[gasps]

187
00:10:53,708 --> 00:10:56,125
I think it would be wise
for us to head to Saubreme

188
00:10:56,208 --> 00:10:58,375
sooner rather than later.

189
00:10:58,458 --> 00:11:00,541
Brian...

190
00:11:00,625 --> 00:11:02,625
Let's go see the Wolf pup.

191
00:11:02,708 --> 00:11:05,125
Though I despise her,
it doesn't matter.

192
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:07,291
You love her.

193
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:10,875
Besides, we need to know
just what Victorique can do.

194
00:11:12,875 --> 00:11:13,875
I've never questioned

195
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:16,416
my daughter's strength.

196
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:20,666
Her intelligence and kindness
are without parallel.

197
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:24,458
There's nothing I believe
in more than her power.

198
00:11:24,541 --> 00:11:26,375
My whole life has
been full of nothing

199
00:11:26,458 --> 00:11:28,875
but humiliation and resentment.

200
00:11:33,125 --> 00:11:35,750
[CORDELIA] She's the only
thing I can count on.

201
00:11:37,625 --> 00:11:39,208
So the "interesting" ghost story

202
00:11:39,291 --> 00:11:41,416
turned out to be another fart
from the brainless newt.

203
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:42,708
Why am I not surprised?

204
00:11:42,791 --> 00:11:43,500
[AVRIL gasps]

205
00:11:43,583 --> 00:11:45,125
I haven't finished yet!

206
00:11:45,208 --> 00:11:46,291
Mm...

207
00:11:46,375 --> 00:11:48,250
[fluttering]

208
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:49,333
[BOTH gasp]

209
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:55,125
Ew! A dove! I hate those
filthy birds with a passion.

210
00:11:55,208 --> 00:11:56,958
They're always trying to
walk on people's heads,

211
00:11:57,041 --> 00:11:58,625
all pitter-patter like.

212
00:12:07,416 --> 00:12:08,750
[gasps]

213
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:10,916
[AVRIL] And just listen to that
creepy noise they make.

214
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:13,541
Proo-proo. Proo-proo.

215
00:12:13,625 --> 00:12:15,375
[AVRIL gasps]

216
00:12:15,458 --> 00:12:17,958
Victorique? Hey!
What happened?

217
00:12:18,041 --> 00:12:20,500
Did that dove try
to touch your hair?

218
00:12:20,583 --> 00:12:22,750
Why are you running away?

219
00:12:24,125 --> 00:12:26,416
[MARQUIS]
The stage has been set.

220
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:29,708
The performance of "The Blue
Rose of Saubreme" at the Phantom

221
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:31,833
will undoubtedly root them
out of whatever hole

222
00:12:31,916 --> 00:12:33,750
they've been hiding in.

223
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:35,750
Then I'll have "it"
reveal the murderer

224
00:12:35,833 --> 00:12:38,791
from that day in front
of them and the country.

225
00:12:38,875 --> 00:12:41,958
For with her
"wellspring of wisdom,"

226
00:12:42,041 --> 00:12:44,041
the small Gray Wolf
with my blood

227
00:12:44,125 --> 00:12:46,625
shall solve the
murder in no time.

228
00:12:46,708 --> 00:12:48,666
[JULIE]
Stop it! Please!

229
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:50,458
--No!
--[NURSE A] Please. Calm down!

230
00:12:50,541 --> 00:12:51,750
Hunting dogs?

231
00:12:51,833 --> 00:12:53,000
[ALL grunting]

232
00:12:53,083 --> 00:12:55,166
I promise that neither
one of us are animals.

233
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:57,458
We just need to get you
undressed for a bath, dear.

234
00:12:57,541 --> 00:12:58,541
[CORDELIA]
It's the pendant.

235
00:12:58,625 --> 00:12:59,833
[ALL gasp]

236
00:12:59,916 --> 00:13:02,250
She's upset because
you tried to take it off.

237
00:13:02,333 --> 00:13:03,250
[JULIE grunts]

238
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:05,458
[CORDELIA]
That seems to be why.

239
00:13:05,541 --> 00:13:07,208
[JULIE cries]

240
00:13:07,291 --> 00:13:09,291
[CORDELIA]
It's important to you, isn't it?

241
00:13:09,375 --> 00:13:10,333
[JULIE]
Huh?

242
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:15,583
I know how you feel.

243
00:13:15,666 --> 00:13:17,500
[NURSE B] Cordelia, you
shouldn't be in here.

244
00:13:17,583 --> 00:13:20,375
Your next bath is not
for three more days.

245
00:13:22,291 --> 00:13:24,083
[CORDELIA]
Before I knew it,

246
00:13:24,166 --> 00:13:27,250
he had me locked up in
a mental institution.

247
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:29,291
In a rare act of kindness,

248
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:32,000
one of the man's sympathetic
servants gave me a picture

249
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:35,791
of my infant daughter as
he tore me away from her.

250
00:13:37,875 --> 00:13:39,791
[CORDELIA]
The child I never wanted

251
00:13:39,875 --> 00:13:43,208
had been forced on me
by that hateful man.

252
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:46,666
[CORDELIA]
And yet...

253
00:13:48,125 --> 00:13:49,250
[CORDELIA]
That night...

254
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:56,583
[CORDELIA] It felt as if
the very mind and soul

255
00:13:56,666 --> 00:13:58,791
that I had been born
with and loved,

256
00:13:58,875 --> 00:14:01,791
that which made up
who I was as a person,

257
00:14:01,875 --> 00:14:04,166
had been torn out of my body.

258
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:06,708
And had taken on its own form.

259
00:14:06,791 --> 00:14:09,083
Right in front of my eyes.

260
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:29,458
[howling]

261
00:14:39,041 --> 00:14:41,166
You're a hard girl
to find, Cordelia.

262
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:43,875
[CORDELIA]
I was eventually rescued

263
00:14:43,958 --> 00:14:47,083
by my red-headed friend,
Brian Roscoe.

264
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:57,583
[VOLUNTEER grunts]
Hey!

265
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:02,083
[laughing]

266
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:05,958
[ROSCOE]
Good job, Cordelia.

267
00:15:06,041 --> 00:15:08,875
Looks like you're starting to
get the hang of it in there.

268
00:15:10,666 --> 00:15:13,250
I've always loved
being on stage.

269
00:15:13,333 --> 00:15:14,750
I know.

270
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:17,958
So, I was thinking we should
celebrate tonight's success?

271
00:15:18,041 --> 00:15:19,500
What are you in the mood for?

272
00:15:23,708 --> 00:15:26,250
[CORDELIA]
I'd like...

273
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:28,625
...to see her.

274
00:15:28,708 --> 00:15:30,166
My daughter.

275
00:15:31,375 --> 00:15:32,875
[CORDELIA]
Several years had passed

276
00:15:32,958 --> 00:15:35,833
since I had been
taken away from her.

277
00:15:35,916 --> 00:15:39,416
I was finally going to
hold my daughter again.

278
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:42,125
But... what I found there...

279
00:15:42,208 --> 00:15:44,041
[CORDELIA gasps]

280
00:15:44,125 --> 00:15:46,875
[CORDELIA]
...was my story repeating.

281
00:15:50,166 --> 00:15:53,541
[CORDELIA] She was now the one
locked up in that cold tower.

282
00:15:53,625 --> 00:15:54,875
Her freedom stolen.

283
00:15:54,958 --> 00:15:57,125
[VICTORIQUE whimpering]

284
00:15:57,208 --> 00:15:59,833
[CORDELIA]
With her cries unanswered.

285
00:15:59,916 --> 00:16:01,666
And her screams forbidden.

286
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:05,208
[whimpering]

287
00:16:05,291 --> 00:16:07,041
Don't worry, my love.

288
00:16:07,125 --> 00:16:09,541
No words are needed.

289
00:16:09,625 --> 00:16:10,458
Take this.

290
00:16:10,541 --> 00:16:12,000
[VICTORIQUE gasps]

291
00:16:15,375 --> 00:16:17,250
[CORDELIA]
As long as you have it with you,

292
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:19,625
I'll always be able to find you.

293
00:16:19,708 --> 00:16:21,375
No matter where you are,

294
00:16:21,458 --> 00:16:24,583
I'll come running
as fast as I can.

295
00:16:24,666 --> 00:16:25,708
[VICTORIQUE gasps]

296
00:16:28,041 --> 00:16:30,041
[gasps]

297
00:16:30,125 --> 00:16:33,750
My sweet little girl...

298
00:16:33,833 --> 00:16:37,791
You are... my entire soul.

299
00:16:37,875 --> 00:16:39,875
[STUDENT A] Watch out!
It's the Golden Fairy!

300
00:16:39,958 --> 00:16:41,166
[STUDENT B]
Huh?

301
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:42,333
[STUDENT E screams]

302
00:16:44,958 --> 00:16:46,791
--[VICTORIQUE yelps]
--[STUDENT F] It fell down!

303
00:16:49,375 --> 00:16:51,541
[STUDENT C]
Is its nose broken?

304
00:16:51,625 --> 00:16:53,458
Oh no, it stood up again.

305
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,625
[VICTORIQUE]
Kujo.

306
00:16:59,708 --> 00:17:01,541
You've always been
able to find me.

307
00:17:01,625 --> 00:17:03,583
No matter where I was.

308
00:17:06,708 --> 00:17:09,833
[VICTORIQUE]
But now... I need to find you.

309
00:17:13,208 --> 00:17:16,375
[VICTORIQUE] I'll search every
inch of this place if I have to.

310
00:17:21,208 --> 00:17:23,125
[BLOIS]
What are you doing?!

311
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:25,125
Let go of me, you
four-eyed lunatic!

312
00:17:25,208 --> 00:17:27,500
I'm not going to let you
take Victorique away again,

313
00:17:27,583 --> 00:17:29,166
you spikey-haired degenerate!

314
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:31,875
S-Say what?! You're crazy-- Ah!

315
00:17:31,958 --> 00:17:33,625
I won't be defeated.

316
00:17:33,708 --> 00:17:35,625
Your dumb drill
doesn't scare me!

317
00:17:35,708 --> 00:17:39,000
In case you haven't noticed,
my hair has tiny drills, too!

318
00:17:39,083 --> 00:17:40,208
[VICTORIQUE]
Miss Cécile.

319
00:17:40,291 --> 00:17:42,166
Run away, I've got him!

320
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:44,041
Where have you been?

321
00:17:44,125 --> 00:17:46,375
[VICTORIQUE] I've been
trying to track down Kujo.

322
00:17:46,458 --> 00:17:47,375
[gasps]

323
00:17:47,458 --> 00:17:49,541
You've come here
to take me away.

324
00:17:49,625 --> 00:17:51,166
Isn't that right?

325
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:52,666
So tell me...

326
00:17:52,750 --> 00:17:55,000
What is it our father
wants this time?

327
00:17:55,083 --> 00:17:56,583
[BLOIS]
Your assignment...

328
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,458
...is to unravel the most
famous unsolved murder

329
00:18:00,541 --> 00:18:02,416
in all of Saubure's history!

330
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:04,375
[VICTORIQUE]
What case is that?

331
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:06,958
[VICTORIQUE]
You can't mean...

332
00:18:07,041 --> 00:18:08,416
Yes.

333
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:11,500
The one that took
place in the palace.

334
00:18:11,583 --> 00:18:13,958
The murder of Queen Coco Rose!

335
00:18:16,708 --> 00:18:17,791
[SOPHIE]
No way!

336
00:18:17,875 --> 00:18:20,333
Tonight's show
can't be sold out!

337
00:18:20,416 --> 00:18:23,625
[KAZUYA sighs]
We actually made it here alive.

338
00:18:23,708 --> 00:18:27,500
[SOLDIERS laughing]

339
00:18:27,583 --> 00:18:29,583
What's with the soldiers?

340
00:18:29,666 --> 00:18:31,125
[SOPHIE]
It's so not fair.

341
00:18:31,208 --> 00:18:32,750
Those servicemen
abused their power

342
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:34,375
and scooped up all the tickets--

343
00:18:34,458 --> 00:18:35,666
Watch where you're walking!

344
00:18:35,750 --> 00:18:37,166
[RUPERT]
That's enough.

345
00:18:39,083 --> 00:18:40,666
[RUPERT]
Please forgive us.

346
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:42,333
Are you all right, mademoiselle?

347
00:18:42,416 --> 00:18:44,416
[SOPHIE]
Oh! Yes.

348
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:46,416
That's good.

349
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:47,916
[ROGER gasps]

350
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,125
I'm sorry.

351
00:18:49,208 --> 00:18:50,791
Let me make it up to you, miss.

352
00:18:50,875 --> 00:18:52,625
We have an extra
ticket to the show.

353
00:18:52,708 --> 00:18:53,958
Please take it.

354
00:18:54,041 --> 00:18:55,958
[SOPHIE gasps]
Seriously?

355
00:18:56,041 --> 00:18:57,458
Glad I almost ran into you!

356
00:18:57,541 --> 00:18:59,000
How rude! This man is your Ki--

357
00:18:59,083 --> 00:19:00,125
Hold your tongue.

358
00:19:00,208 --> 00:19:01,333
Need I remind you again

359
00:19:01,416 --> 00:19:04,125
that we're here on a
private matter, Roger?

360
00:19:08,875 --> 00:19:09,916
Well, that was bizarre.

361
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,375
Ah, they must be my
guardian angels.

362
00:19:12,458 --> 00:19:14,375
Sent down by God to
give this ticket to me.

363
00:19:14,458 --> 00:19:16,083
[CROWD gasps]

364
00:19:17,708 --> 00:19:20,166
Allow me to introduce to you...

365
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:22,708
...the two beautiful women
who will be playing Coco Rose

366
00:19:22,791 --> 00:19:24,166
in tonight's show.

367
00:19:24,250 --> 00:19:25,875
We have palace Coco.

368
00:19:25,958 --> 00:19:27,833
And country house Coco!

369
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:30,625
The audience will get to watch
both actresses' portrayals.

370
00:19:30,708 --> 00:19:33,041
[SOPHIE whines]
I can't see anything!

371
00:19:33,125 --> 00:19:34,375
I'm sorry to leave
you like this.

372
00:19:34,458 --> 00:19:35,583
[SOPHIE growls]

373
00:19:35,666 --> 00:19:37,250
But I really need to
go shopping right now.

374
00:19:37,333 --> 00:19:38,291
[SOPHIE]
I see them!

375
00:19:38,375 --> 00:19:39,541
Hey! Look over here,
pretty ladies!

376
00:19:39,625 --> 00:19:41,458
I'm heading off to the shops!

377
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,041
[KAZUYA]
Christmas seems amazing!

378
00:19:51,125 --> 00:19:53,625
It's so different from the
Obon or New Year's festivals

379
00:19:53,708 --> 00:19:54,916
that I'm used to.

380
00:19:56,666 --> 00:19:59,291
[KAZUYA] I wonder what
I should get Victorique?

381
00:19:59,375 --> 00:20:00,625
Perhaps a new pipe?

382
00:20:00,708 --> 00:20:02,958
With candy hidden inside?

383
00:20:03,041 --> 00:20:04,541
Or maybe...

384
00:20:05,916 --> 00:20:06,875
[KAZUYA gasps]

385
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:10,083
What's this?

386
00:20:10,166 --> 00:20:12,041
That? It's a locket I created

387
00:20:12,125 --> 00:20:15,375
using one of the gold coins
from the king's coronation.

388
00:20:21,666 --> 00:20:23,333
[KAZUYA] It reminds me
of the precious pendant

389
00:20:23,416 --> 00:20:25,833
Cordelia gave
Victorique as a child.

390
00:20:29,208 --> 00:20:31,000
[KAZUYA]
She sacrificed that necklace

391
00:20:31,083 --> 00:20:34,583
in order to keep me from
falling to my death.

392
00:20:34,666 --> 00:20:36,875
As long as she had the pendant,

393
00:20:36,958 --> 00:20:38,750
Victorique's mother
would be able to save her

394
00:20:38,833 --> 00:20:41,583
from any danger,
no matter what.

395
00:20:43,166 --> 00:20:44,958
[KAZUYA]
It's time I replaced it.

396
00:20:45,041 --> 00:20:46,958
With one from me.

397
00:20:48,958 --> 00:20:52,125
[KAZUYA] She'll be safe as long
as she wears this locket.

398
00:20:52,208 --> 00:20:54,791
But it won't be her mother
that comes to the rescue.

399
00:20:54,875 --> 00:20:56,750
I'll be the one that saves her.

400
00:20:57,791 --> 00:20:58,708
[KAZUYA groans]

401
00:20:58,791 --> 00:21:01,625
[CROWD murmuring]

402
00:21:01,708 --> 00:21:03,666
[SERGIUS]
A great wind will blow.

403
00:21:03,750 --> 00:21:04,875
[KAZUYA gasps]

404
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:14,083
[SERGIUS] I'm told that
many years from now,

405
00:21:14,166 --> 00:21:15,791
a great wind will blow.

406
00:21:15,875 --> 00:21:19,708
The strength of it will cause
our entire world to shake.

407
00:21:22,875 --> 00:21:24,208
[VICTORIQUE]
Kujo...

408
00:21:24,291 --> 00:21:27,208
Please forgive me for
not being able to find you.

409
00:21:27,291 --> 00:21:29,250
I tried so hard.

410
00:21:29,333 --> 00:21:32,416
[SERGIUS] Your bodies will
be weightless in its grasp.

411
00:21:35,583 --> 00:21:36,541
[KAZUYA groans]

412
00:21:37,791 --> 00:21:40,166
[KAZUYA gasps]
Excuse me.

413
00:21:40,250 --> 00:21:42,958
[SERGIUS] The two of you will
be blown apart by the winds.

414
00:21:43,041 --> 00:21:46,250
Never to be put
back together again.

415
00:21:49,291 --> 00:21:50,958
[SERGIUS]
However...

416
00:21:51,041 --> 00:21:52,583
[VICTORIQUE]
Kujo?

417
00:21:52,666 --> 00:21:55,500
I hope the prophecy
isn't coming true.

418
00:21:55,583 --> 00:21:58,083
That we still have
time together...

419
00:21:58,166 --> 00:22:02,000
...before we're
blown apart forever.

420
00:22:02,083 --> 00:22:04,458
[SERGIUS]
Your two hearts are connected.

421
00:22:04,541 --> 00:22:06,500
And always will be.

422
00:22:07,541 --> 00:22:10,583
[AVRIL panting]

423
00:22:10,666 --> 00:22:12,458
[sighs]

424
00:22:12,541 --> 00:22:15,500
 Where in the world did
that girl run off to now?

425
00:22:15,583 --> 00:22:16,708
[gasps]

426
00:22:20,750 --> 00:22:23,500
[AVRIL]
"The second storm is coming"?

427
00:22:29,708 --> 00:22:33,708
[CORDELIA] Any day now, the
second storm will be upon us.

428
00:22:34,750 --> 00:22:38,291
[CORDELIA] The time has
come to show me your power.

429
00:22:38,375 --> 00:22:40,875
My sweet daughter...

430
00:22:40,958 --> 00:22:42,416
My soul...

431
00:22:42,500 --> 00:22:43,833
My everything...

432
00:24:14,875 --> 00:24:16,916
[CÉCILE]
You can call me the trunk fairy!

433
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:19,416
I'm here to protect
you, Victorique!

434
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:22,416
Trunk, trunk, trunk!

435
00:24:22,500 --> 00:24:25,000
[VICTORIQUE]
Now I feel even more nervous.

